				<div class="three-column-one">
					<%=image_tag "/assets/team/tara_mccarthy.jpg", class: "img-responsive" %>
					<h3>Tara McCarthy MS, RDN</h3>
					<h4>Co-Founder & Chief Dietitian</h4>
					<p>Tara has been a Registered Dietitian Nutritionist (RDN) for over 16 years. She been on the staff at Boston Children’s Hospital since 2001, during which time, she has cared for a wide variety of patients including those challenged by food allergies, celiac disease, EoE, FPIES and CSID. In addition to counseling at Boston Medical Center, BC Campus School, (a school for developmentally delayed children), and in the homes of many families, Tara also has taught Nutrition courses at Northeastern University and mentored dozens of RDNs. Tara lives in Milton, MA with her husband and three children. </p>
				</div>
				<div class="three-column-one">
					<%=image_tag "/assets/team/lauren_deal.JPG", class: "img-responsive" %>
					<h3>Lauren Deal</h3>
					<h4>Executive Chef</h4>
					<p>Lauren has a love for food and the role that food plays in bringing families together. She began her journey with food as a little girl, cooking at home with her mother, and decided to reinforce her upbringing with culinary school in Italy. She has cooked professionally since 2004 in many highly regarded restaurants. Prior to joining the Kindrdfood team, Lauren was the Sous Chef at Chez Panisse Café in Berkleley, CA. Lauren currently lives in the San Francisco Bay Area with her husband, daughter and Labrador Winston.</p>
				<!-- 			<p>Add food allergy connection</p> -->
