				<%=image_tag "/assets/team/liz_hait.jpg", class: "img-responsive" %>
					<h3>Elizabeth J. Hait, MD MPH</h3>
					<h4>Co-Founder & Senior Medical Advisor</h4>
					<p>Dr. Elizabeth Hait is an Assistant Professor of Pediatrics at Harvard Medical School in Boston, MA. She currently treats patients at Boston Children’s Hospital, Brigham and Women’s Hospital and Beth Israel Deaconess Hospital, where she is a staff pediatric gastroenterologist. Dr. Hait is the co-medical director of the Eosinophilic Gastrointestinal Diseases program at Boston Children’s Hospital. She teaches at Harvard Medical School and is involved in multiple areas of research including allergic gastrointestinal disorders, inflammatory bowel disease, and GI environmental health exposures. Dr. Hait lives in Needham, MA with her husband and two sons.</p>
